cal condensation yields arginine in modern and plausible prebiotic analogs; (Smith et al., 2019; Bernal et al., 2019)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_012\",\n      \"name\": \"Formate \u2192 glycolaldehyde (Borate-catalyzed Formose reaction)\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_005\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_008\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"borate minerals\", null],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"300-370K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"borate\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"alkaline\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Formate undergoes aldol condensation and borate stabilization to form glycolaldehyde.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Formose reaction is stabilized by borate minerals; (Ricardo et al., 2004; Sutherland et al., 2016)\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"pathways\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrothermal Greigite \u2192 Surface Formose \u2192 Strecker \u2192 Biochemical path\",\n      \"description\": \"CO2 reduction to formate (greigite), formate \u2192 glycolaldehyde (borate), glycolaldehyde + NH3 + HCN (montmorillonite) \u2192 aminonitrile, aminonitriles condense to ornithine, ornithine with argininosuccinate produces arginine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_012\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_005\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_009\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P2\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrothermal Magnetite \u2192 Pyruvate \u2192 Alanine \u2192 Transamination\",\n      \"description\": \"CO2 + H2 (magnetite, hydrothermal) generates pyruvate, pyruvate + NH3 (pyrite) yields alanine, alanine + \u03b1-ketoglutarate transaminated to ornithine (phosphate), ornithine \u2192 argininosuccinate \u2192 arginine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_002\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_007\", \"